President Obama has nominated Professor Scott L. Silliman and William B. Pollard, III to serve on the United States Court of Military Commission Review. Professor Silliman is a law professor at Duke University, specializing in national security law, military law, and the law of armed conflict. He has also served as the Executive Director of the Center on Law, Ethics and National Security at Duke. William B. Pollard, III is a partner at a law firm in New York City, specializing in complex civil and white collar criminal cases. He previously worked as an Assistant United States Attorney in the Southern District of New York. Both nominees have extensive experience in military and civilian law, making them qualified to protect national security interests and uphold judicial standards.